<NOTE>Safety Group Says 5 Million Ford-made Cars Pose Hazard</NOTE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A auto safety watchdog group says badly
designed fuel filler pipes on 5 million Ford Motor Co. cars pose a
fire danger that already has caused more than 200 deaths.
   Officials of the Institute for Injury Reduction said Thursday
that the company should spend $250 million to recall and fix the
fuel tank assemblies on the cars, a variety of models made since
1965.
   Ford spokesman Jerald terHorst said the company is not aware of
any hazardous condition that would warrant a recall of older models
and that Ford has confidence in the safety of its cars' fuel systems.
