<SECOND>AM-BRF--Thailand-US,0143</SECOND>
<HEAD>U.S. Plastic Surgeons Arrive in Thailand for Charity</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A group of Chicago doctors and other
medical personnel arrived Friday to operate free-of-charge on 100
Thai children born with cleft lips and palates, a Thai doctor said.
   The group, from Chicago, will leave Monday for Chaiyaphum in
northeastern Thailand, where children from one to 12 years of age
await operations to correct the birth defect, said the doctor, Dusit
Sundaranu.
   The 16 Americans _ seven doctors and nine other medical
specialists _ will stay for six days. Thai doctors will assist the
team and arrange follow-up care.
   Dr. Craig Bradley, the plastic surgeon leading the group, has
said the doctors would volunteer their time and pay their own fare.
Some funds for supplies were provided by Rush-Presbyterian-St.Luke's
Medical Center in Chicago, where Bradley works.
