<SECOND>AM-Honey Production,80</SECOND>
<HEAD>Honey Output Down 7 Percent Last Year</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Honey production dropped 7 percent last year to
212 million pounds, the Agriculture Department said Friday.
   About 3.2 million colonies produced honey in 1988, a decline of
less than 1 percent, according to the USDA report. But the yield of
honey per colony dropped to 66.4 pounds, down from 71.1 pounds in
1987.
   ``Some states had excellent production while production in other
states suffered from drought and disease,'' the report said.
