<FIRST>u f AM-OilPrices     02-10 0175</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Oil Prices,0184</SECOND>
<HEAD>Energy Futures Fall Sharply</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Home heating oil prices fell sharply Friday,
taking other energy prices down with them.
   On the New York Mercantile Exchange, the March contract for
heating oil fell 1.25 cents to 47.36 cents a gallon.
   ``The heating oil market had every reason to rally'' but was
unable to do so, said Andrew Lebow, an energy futures analyst with
E.D.&amp;F. Man International Futures Inc.
   Severe winter weather in the United States should have given
heating oil prices a boost, but warmer weather overseas and an
abundance of oil stocks here and abroad depressed prices, Lebow said.
   The gloomy news spilled over to the markets for crude oil and
gasoline.
   The March contract for West Texas Intermediate, the benchmark
grade of U.S. crude, dropped 28 cents to $17.11 a barrel, and the
March contract for unleaded gasoline declined 0.79 cent to 47.57
cents a gallon.
   ``It was a heating oil-led decline,'' Lebow said.
   Rising stockpiles of gasoline took a further toll on gas prices,
analysts said.
</TEXT>
