<DOCNO> AP890210-0295 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-02-10-89 2352EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f AM-Grace-Sales     02-10 0210</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Grace-Sales,0219</SECOND>
<HEAD>W.R. Grace Considering Sale of Interest in One or More Businesses</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   W.R. Grace &amp; Co. said Friday it is considering
selling a stake in one or more of its businesses so it can channel
more capital into its core chemicals segment.
   Grace said it was considering the possible sale of a minority
interest in its specialty businesses, which include cocoa,
distribution, textiles and agriculture.
   The company also said it was looking into the possible sale of an
interest in its natural resources division. No price tags were named
for any of the businesses.
   J. Peter Grace, the company's chairman, said in a statement the
firm wanted to concentrate on its core specialty chemical business
``while insuring the necessary capital to support its non-specialty
chemical activities.''
   ``With high capital requirements arising from growth and earnings
opportunities in specialty chemicals, as well as other Grace niche
businesses, we are actively evaluating the possible redeployment of
capital,'' Grace said.
   The company said its specialty chemical business had $3.1 billion
in sales and $237 million in operating income last year.
   In its statement, Grace said it expected to have $338 million in
capital expenditures for Grace Specialty Chemicals Co. this year, up
from $288 million in 1988.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
